fields.name: 🌶️ Dry Garlic Chutney  (The Soul of Vada Pav

fields.text: Season chicken with taco seasoning and cook in a pan until done.
Warm tortillas in a dry pan or microwave.
Shred lettuce and dice tomatoes.
Grate cheese and cut lime into wedges.
Slice cooked chicken into strips.
Assemble tacos with chicken, lettuce, tomatoes, and cheese.
Serve with sour cream and lime wedges.
Cook quinoa according to package instructions.
Roast diced sweet potato at 200°C for 25 minutes.
Steam broccoli until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain and rinse chickpeas.
Slice avocado just before serving.
Mix tahini, lemon juice, and olive oil for dressing.
Arrange all ingredients in bowls and drizzle with dressing.
Preheat oven to 190°C.
Cream butter with both sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla extract.
Mix flour, baking soda, and salt in separate bowl.
Gradually add dry ingredients to wet ingredients.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded tablespoons of dough onto baking sheets.
Bake for 10-12 minutes until edges are golden.
Cool on baking sheets for 5 minutes before transferring.
Wash spinach thoroughly.
Peel and slice banana.
Core and chop apple.
Add all ingredients to blender.
Blend until smooth and creamy.
Add more coconut water if needed for desired consistency.
Serve immediately in chilled glasses.

Make the Batata Vada (Spiced Potato Fritter)
- Boil & mash potatoes (about 3–4 medium ones).
- Temper spices: Heat oil, add mustard seeds, curry leaves, hing, chopped green chilies, garlic, and ginger. Sauté until aromatic.
- Mix with potatoes: Add turmeric, salt, and coriander leaves. Shape into round balls.

Prepare the Batter
- Mix besan (gram flour) with a pinch of baking soda, turmeric, salt, and water to make a thick, lump-free batter.
- Dip each potato ball into the batter and deep fry until golden brown.

Make the Chutneys
- Green chutney: Blend coriander, mint, green chilies, garlic, lemon juice, and salt.
- Tamarind chutney (optional): Tamarind pulp, jaggery, chili powder, cumin.
- Dry garlic chutney: Roasted garlic, coconut, red chili powder, and salt.

Assemble the Vada Pav
- Slice a ladi pav (soft bun) without cutting all the way through.
- Spread green chutney, tamarind chutney, and dry garlic chutney.
- Place the hot vada inside, press gently, and serve with fried green chilies.
Cook spaghetti in salted boiling water until al dente.
Fry pancetta until crisp.
Beat eggs and mix with grated Parmesan.
Drain pasta, reserving some water.
Combine pasta, pancetta, and egg mixture off the heat, adding pasta water as needed.
Serve with extra cheese and black pepper.
Chop all vegetables into bite-sized pieces.
Heat oil in a wok and add garlic.
Add vegetables and stir fry for 5-7 minutes.
Add soy sauce and cook for 2 more minutes.
Serve hot with rice or noodles.
Marinate chicken in yogurt and spices for 1 hour.
Grill or pan-fry chicken until cooked through.
Simmer tomato puree with spices and cream.
Add chicken to sauce and cook for 10 minutes.
Serve with rice or naan.
Chop tomatoes and cucumber.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Drizzle with olive oil and toss.
Serve chilled.
Boil water and dissolve miso paste.
Add tofu, seaweed, and green onions.
Simmer for 5 minutes and serve.
Cook onion and bell pepper until soft.
Add tomatoes and paprika, simmer until thickened.
Make wells and crack eggs into sauce.
Cover and cook until eggs are set.
Serve with bread.
Warm tortilla wraps.
Fill with falafel, lettuce, tomato, and tahini sauce.
Wrap and serve.
Caramelize onions in butter.
Add beef broth and simmer.
Ladle soup into bowls, top with baguette and cheese.
Broil until cheese is melted.
Soak rice noodles in warm water.
Stir fry shrimp and tofu.
Add noodles, sauce, and bean sprouts.
Top with peanuts and serve.
Mash banana and mix with egg, milk, and flour.
Add baking powder and mix until smooth.
Cook pancakes on a greased skillet until golden.
Serve with syrup or fruit.
